text: Kazayak-Kutush () is a rural locality (a village) in Ulu-Telyaksky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 41 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 82 km from Iglino, 12 km from Ulu-Telyak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kazayak-Kutush
